    <text xml:id="t1">
        <body xml:id="t1-body">
            
            <pb n="1" facs="#rb028a" xml:id="t1-body-pb1"/>
            
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" ref="#ZEI" key="ZEI"><choice><sic>Zeitun</sic><corr>Zeitoun</corr></choice> Camp</name>
                    <lb/>
                    near <name type="place" ref="#CAR" key="CAR">Cairo</name>.
                    <lb/>
                    <date when="1915-03-15">15. 3. 1915.</date>
                </dateline>
                <lb/>
                <lb/>
                <salute>Dear <name type="person" ref="#EJO" key="EJO">Mrs Edgar Jones</name></salute>:
            </opener>
            
            <p>
                Thank you very
                <lb/>
                much indeed for your
                <lb/>
                letter.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                I cannot tell you
                <lb/>
                at all what our future
                <lb/>
                movements will be, but
                <lb/>
                in the event of our coming
                <lb/>
                to <name type="place" ref="#ENG" key="ENG">England</name> I will
                <lb/>
                certainly let you know.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                Here we are very
                
                <pb n="2" facs="#rb028b" xml:id="t1-body-x4-pb1"/>
                
                comfortable &amp; living in a
                <lb/>
                lovely climate : I am
                <lb/>
                afraid we are very far
                <lb/>
                from realising the horrors
                <lb/>
                of the war.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                <name type="person" ref="#CYH" key="CYH">Cyril Hayter</name> is with
                <lb/>
                us &amp; sends his kind
                <lb/>
                regards.  <name type="person" ref="#CHI" key="CHI">Chilton Hayter</name>
                <lb/>
                is I believe coming out
                <lb/>
                with some of the later
                <lb/>
                reinforcements.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                The health of everyone
                <lb/>
                is excellent, as indeed
                
                <pb n="3" facs="#rb028c" xml:id="t1-body-x6-pb1"/>
                
                it could not very well
                <lb/>
                be otherwise in this
                <lb/>
                splendid climate.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                All the men are
                <lb/>
                very keen and we do 
                <lb/>
                hope to be given an 
                <lb/>
                opportunity to do some
                <lb/>
                serious work before long.
            </p>
            
            <p>
                We were not employed
                <lb/>
                on the Canal.  Horsemen
                <lb/>
                are rather at a discount
                <lb/>
                in trench fighting.
            </p>
            
            <pb n="4" facs="#rb028d" xml:id="t1-body-pb2"/>
            
            <p>
                I hope that you &amp;
                <lb/>
                your family are all well,
                <lb/>
                and also that you will
                <lb/>
                not suffer in any way
                <lb/>
                by the war.
            </p>
            
            <closer>
                <salute>
                    With kind regards to
                    <lb/>
                    your husband &amp; yourself.
                    <lb/>
                    Believe me
                    <lb/>
                    Sincerely yours.
                </salute>
                <lb/>
                <signed>
                    <name type="person" ref="#RTB" key="RTB">Roy. Bruce.</name>
                </signed>
            </closer>
            <pb facs="#rb028envf" xml:id="t1-body-pb3"/>
            <pb facs="#rb028envb" xml:id="t1-body-pb4"/>
        </body>
    </text>
